I would prefer a long string to _not_ get split into multiple lines, even if it contains expressions. When there are no expressions, Prettier correctly lets a long string go beyond the `print-width` limit.

I can't decide if this is a bug or a personal preference, but it's been creating weird hard to read code in our codebase. We can clean most of it up by simplifying our expressions, but there's only so short we can go.

I know the goal of prettier is to standardize on a style, but it is also difficult since this did not come out at the same time as the language. 

Our team uses the exact same style as prettier except placement for `else` statements. It is effectively blocking us from adopting this awesome library.

We prefer break before `else` to allow for cleaner comments.

```js
// This does something
if (a) {
}
// This does something else if
else if {

}
// This does something else
else {

}
```

Which is nicer than.

```js
// This does something
if (a) {

// This does something else if
} else if {

// This does something else
} else {

}
```

However this is preference and would be awesome if this was added as an option to prettier.

